publisher			Stupid Stupid Games							
publish_time	 2016年6月15日		
desc_long								关于这款游戏							You think your life is tough? Meet Johnny Graves - The Unchosen One.  It’s 1979 in New York. Johnny Graves is a former agent of Hell and Satan needs him back desperately to finish the job he started over two centuries ago. Now the devil sends his beasts with wrath to bring Johnny back to the fold. Johnny has one night to close the gates of Hell and prevent Satan himself from coming across the mortal divide.Johnny Graves—The Unchosen One is an action RPG set in an urban fantasy environment. It is a story-driven single player game for Windows PC, developed using Unity 3D. The Early Access version offers up to 20 minutes of hack and slash gameplay (although a seasoned player might get through it faster)! This game is the first part of the Night of the Creatures trilogy. The next two games will continue the action that takes place during the one night in 1979, but seen through the eyes of different protagonists.  Among our many products (TBA) that take place in the Agents of Armageddon universe, Johnny Graves—The Unchosen One is our first PC game. In the Agents of Armageddon storyworld, the secret histories of humankind are revealed. Our various products are windows into its 250 000 year long timeline.Early Access Features:1/7 levels  1/6 magic bullets & infinite normal bullets0/1 blink 0/3 boss fights 2/10 enemy monsters (spiders and zombies)2/8 storytelling sequences Playtime estimate 20 minutes10% of the finished game3/3 languages (English, German and Russian)Please note, since The Night of the Creatures –trilogy will be released periodically, some features will not be available in the first launch and are unlocked at a later stage. Please bear in mind that the very first Early Access version is not as satisfying as the finished game will be, in terms of visual effects and playability. We hope that in your darkest, most frustrating hour of buggy gameplay, you remember that you did not purchase a defective game; you invested in our finished product, and in time, that you shall have. Below is a list of bugs we are aware of and working on. If you come across any bugs that are not on our list, please let us know!List of known bugs:In rare cases you might get stuck on level geometry.List of features you might expect, but aren't there yet – will be added:Character developmentSave game featureAdvanced quality settings						
